**** Except Pulpit Speech and Oral Communication.

<hr><center><h2>                                     IV. FACILITIES, EQUIPMENT, AND OPPORTUNITIES</h2></center><BR>

You will have a special academic advisor until you graduate.  The advisor will help you with your
choice of courses, class schedules, and other matters of an academic nature.  He will also assist you in
choosing a law school and will guide you through the Application process.  The coordinating prelaw
advisor will advise all interested students about legal education even if they are majoring in other
Academic majors.
<P>
The Law School Admissions Test (LSAT) is one of the Admissions requirements to law school.  Your
advisor will help you with registration and preparation for this test.
<P>
Prelaw forums are held occasionally.  In these meetings we feature talks from practicing Christian
attorneys and current law school Students, and discussions of ethical issues with which the law deals.
<P>
The productions of the University Classic Players and Opera Association will enable you in four years
to see several Shakespearean plays and grand operas performed on Campus.  Every year there are also
frequent recitals and student performances in theater, speech, and music.
<P>
The University Debate Association provides opportunity for you to compete in debate as a member of
your society.  Each society participates in several elimination contests throughout the school year to
determine the winner of the University cup which is awarded during Commencement week.  The
University also sponsors debate teams which compete in the National Cross-Examination Debate
Association tournaments several times throughout the year.  Over the years our teams have established
an outstanding record and an excellent reputation in competition at the national and regional levels.
<P>
Forensic teams, which represent Bob Jones University at intercollegiate forensic tournaments during each
school year, consistently have made fine records in competition with other major schools in the Southeast.
<P>
Our Modern Language Laboratory, open six days a week from morning till night, contains the latest
state-of-the-art recording and listening equipment, providing you with a unique opportunity to perfect
your language skills.  We have 28 individual tape player/recorder stations plus another 7 stations which
are serviced by a control console.  Thus, we have the capaCity to play 30 different programs at any given
time.  The laboratory also features an Apple IIe computer.  You may use these facilities without paying
a lab fee.
<P>
<a href="/whatsnew/chapel/">Chapel services are held every morning</A>, Monday through Friday.  These services are a source of great
inspiration to Students.  Four days a week the Chapel message is brought by the Chancellor or <a href="/aboutbju/president/">President</a>
when on the Campus, and in their absence by selected speakers.  One day each week the Chapel period
is devoted to the meetings of various literary societies.  Two meetings each month are devoted to
Missionary programs and speakers.
<P>
The annual spring <a href="/special/bibleconf/">Bible Conference</a> is one of the outstanding features of the University and Academy
year.  Your regular academic work will be suspended for the Conference, during which you will hear
messages from outstanding Bible teachers, pastors, and evangelists.
<P>
<a href="/aboutbju/places/library/">The modern Mack Library</A>, with 90,000 square feet of floor space and seating for over 1400 Students,
will give you access to 231,000 volumes, 1100 current periodical subscriptions, and more than 10,500
recordings.  An interlibrary loan program is available through OCLC, a national database, for books not
held in our library.<a href="/aboutbju/places/fitness/">The Fremont Fitness Center gives you</A> the opportunity to enjoy the benefits of a health club right on
Campus at no additional cost to you.  You can keep yourself in top-notch physical condition through the
use of its state-of-the-art exercise equipment, racquetball courts, spa, and sauna.

<P>
If you are planning to live on Campus, you will be glad to know that <a href="/studentlife/dorm/">all of our Dormitories are</A>air-
conditioned, have wall-to-wall carpeting, and have a phone in each room.  You will be able to make long-
distance calls home directly from your room and have them automatically placed on your school bill.
<P>
All of our classrooms are air-conditioned, and there are awnings over the sidewalks to keep you dry when
it is raining.  <a href="/whatsnew/menu/">The Dining Common serves 8,500 delicious meals</A> a day, and the Snack Shop and
Bookstore <a href="/aboutbju/places/stucenter/">in the Student Center</a> carry just about anything you'll need.
<P>
You will find the finest Christian young people in the country are your fellow Students, and without
trying too hard, you may end up marrying one of them!
<P>


<hr><center><h2>                             V. ABOUT THE FACULTY</h2></center><BR>

Because of its interdisciplinary nature, our prelaw program draws faculty from various University
departments.  These instructors, most of whom have graduate degrees in their field of specialty, enrich
the program through their variety of expertise and backgrounds.  You will thus be taught by experts in
writing, public speaking, constitutional History, government, etc., and you have the assurance that all
subject matter is taught from a Biblical perspective.  The coordinating prelaw advisor has a Ph.D. in
American legal History.



<hr><center><h2>                    VI. CAREER OPPORTUNITIES AND PLACEMENT</h2></center><BR>

Although Admissions to law school is highly competitive, Academically qualified graduates of Bob Jones
University have had a 100 percent acceptance rate to law school over the last decade.  They have gone
to leading institutions in many states and have made outstanding records.  The top 1985 graduate from
Harvard Law School was a BJU alumnus.  Some years ago the Supreme Court of South Carolina
published guidelines for undergraduate prelaw curriculum, and we found that our program met every
specific suggestion.  Our graduates excel in law school because of our emphasis; and with our focus on
communication, our graduates excel in this critical area which tends to be a great difficulty for many law
Students.



<hr><center><h2>                      VII. BJU:  AN AFFORDABLE EDUCATION</h2></center><BR>

Enclosed is an expense sheet detailing the cost of attending Bob Jones University.  When you compare
our charges to those of other private Colleges, we think you will be pleasantly surprised.  We believe we
offer a Student more value for his dollar than anyone else in America.  And to help you see how
affordable "the Opportunity Place" can be for you, we have enclosed a financial analysis form that you
can use to evaluate your own situation.  Your Admissions Counselor or the Director of Student Financial
Aid would be happy to discuss this with you if you have any questions.
<hr><h2><center> HOW TO TAKE THE NEXT STEP. . . </h2></center>
<P>
If you can see yourself in the career described in the profile, then a great opportunity awaits you at
Bob Jones University.  It is the opportunity for the premier Christian college experience in all the world.
It is the opportunity for learning, for fun, and for developing New Friendships.  It is the opportunity to
prepare for a lifetime of service for the Lord . . .
<P>
Simply fill out the <a href="/admissions/information/application.html">enclosed application form</a> and return it in the envelope provided.  Be sure to enclose
the small application fee.  Then get ready for a life-changing experience which more than 60,000 young
people already know about. . .
<p>
The Opportunity Place...God's Special Place for You.<BR>
