</pre>

<p>* If you are planning your career in corporate accounting you will take
these courses. If you are planning to go to graduate school and getting
a CPA, you will substitute Introduction to Calculus for Math of Finance
and may take any accounting elective for Financial Statement Analysis.
** Financial Theory and Applications or Advanced Financial Management
<br>
<a name="facil"><hr><center><h2>IV. FACILITIES, EQUIPMENT, AND OPPORTUNITIES</h2></center></a>

<p>
<br>Two completely equipped computer laboratories are available for your
use. There are 32 386 SXs, 33 IBM AT (286) compatibles, 24 IBM PCs, one
AT&amp;T 3B2/600 UNIX computer with 10 access terminals linked to a Burroughs
6800 mainframe computer, as well as 5 laser printers. We also have 30 Apple
Macintosh SEs and a wide variety of software packages including Quattro
Pro, Microsoft Works, WordPerfect, Turbo Pascal, and many others that are
currently in use in the business world.
<p>Two separate computer laboratories are maintained for the use of business Students.
These laboratories are dedicated to word processing and office automation and are equipped with
48 IBM-compatible computers, 3 laser printers, 42 electronic typewriters,
and 12 dictaphone/transcribers.
<p>As a part of the University Business Association, a Campus organization comprised of Students in the various business majors,
you will have an opportunity to become Acquainted with successful Christian
business people who speak at the regular meetings. The emphasis of UBA
is to help prepare you to be an effective testimony for Christ in the business
world. In addition, this organization operates an Investment Club that
manages a portfolio of real stocks. Also, special office-related forums
are held so office administration majors will have the opportunity to meet
business people who have special expertise in their particular area of
interest.
<p><a href="/aboutbju/places/library/">The modern Mack Library</A>, with 90,000 square feet of floor space
and seating for over 1400 Students, will give you access to 231,000 volumes,
1100 current periodical subscriptions, and more than 10,500 recordings.
An interlibrary loan program is available through OCLC, a national database,
for books not held in our library.
<p><a href="/whatsnew/chapel/">Chapel services are held every morning</A>,Monday through Friday. These services are a source of great inspiration
to Students. Four days a week the Chapel message is brought by the Chancellor
or <a href="/aboutbju/president/">President</a> when on the Campus, and in their absence by selected speakers.
One day each week the Chapel period is devoted to the meetings of various
literary societies. Two meetings each month are devoted to Missionary programs
and speakers.
<p>The  is one of the outstanding
features of the University and Academy year. Your regular academic work
will be suspended for the Conference, during which you will hear messages
from outstanding Bible teachers, pastors, and evangelists.
<p> All Students have opportunity to participate in the University's athletic program. Through
a well-integrated program of intramural athletic competition, a very high
percentage of Student participation is possible. You will have the opportunity
to compete in a wide variety of both team and individual sports including
soccer, speedball, basketball, softball, track, volleyball, tennis, swimming,
badminton, judo, table tennis, racquetball, archery, wrestling, and indoor
soccer.
<p><a href="/aboutbju/places/fitness/">The Fremont Fitness Center gives you</A> the opportunity to enjoy the
benefits of a health club right on Campus at no additional cost to you.
You can keep yourself in top-notch physical condition through the use of
its state-of-the-art exercise equipment, racquetball courts, spa, and sauna.
<p>If you are planning to live on Campus, you will be glad to know that all
of our Dormitories are air-conditioned, have wall-to-wall carpeting, and
have a phone in each room. You will be able to make long-distance calls
home directly from your room and have them automatically placed on your
school bill.
<p>All of our classrooms are air-conditioned, and there are awnings
over the sidewalks to keep you dry when it is raining.<a href="/whatsnew/menu/">The Dining Common serves 8,500 delicious meals</A> a day, and the Snack Shop and Bookstore in
<a href="/aboutbju/places/stucenter/">the Student Center</a> carry just about anything you'll need.
<p>You will find the finest Christian young people in the country are your fellow Students,
and without trying too hard, you may end up marrying one of them!  <BR>
<a name="faculty"><hr><center><h2>V. ABOUT THE FACULTY </h2></center></a>

<p>
<br>All of the faculty members in the Division of Accounting are Certified
Public Accountants. Their average teaching experience is eight years; and
since each has worked for either a public accounting firm or a Fortune
500 company, they bring a significant background of practical experience
as practicing accountants.
<p>
<a name="oppor"><hr><center><h2>VI. CAREER OPPORTUNITIES AND PLACEMENT</h2></center></a>

<p>
<br>Five of the top six accounting firms in the United States recruit annually
on the Campus for our graduating accounting majors. Approximately 30 percent
of our accounting graduates accept positions with these companies. A special
CPA review course will be available to you during your final year of study
to prepare you for the CPA examination. On a recent CPA examination, several
of our recent graduates passed the entire examination on the first try.
For the last five years our graduating seniors have scored above the 60th
percentile on the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants Level
II examinations. Several graduate schools in accounting recruit annually
on our Campus as a service to those students who wish to go on to further
study.
<br>
<a name="finan"><hr><center><h2>VII. BJU: AN AFFORDABLE EDUCATION</h2></center></a>
<p>
<br>Enclosed is an expense sheet detailing the cost of attending Bob Jones
University. When you compare our charges to those of other private Colleges,
we think you will be pleasantly surprised. We believe we offer a Student
more value for his dollar than anyone else in America. And to help you
see how affordable &quot;the Opportunity Place&quot; can be for you, we
have enclosed a financial analysis form that you can use to evaluate your
own situation. Your Admissions Counselor or the Director of Student Financial
Aid would be happy to discuss this with you if you have any questions.


<p>
<a name="next"><hr><center><h2>HOW TO TAKE THE NEXT STEP. . .</h2></center></a>

<p>
<br>If you can see yourself in the career described in the profile, then
a great opportunity awaits you at Bob Jones University. It is the opportunity
for the premier Christian college experience in all the world. It is the
opportunity for learning, for fun, and for developing New Friendships.
It is the opportunity to prepare for a lifetime of service for the Lord
. . .
<p>
Simply fill out the <a href="/admissions/information/application.html">enclosed
application form</a> and return it in the envelope provided. Be sure to
enclose the small application fee. Then get ready for a life-changing
experience which more than 60,000 young people already know about. . .
The Opportunity Place...God's Special Place for You.
<br>
