<TITLE> Radio and Television major </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body><br><br><center><img src="/graphics/bjcrest.gif"></center><br>
<hr><center><h2>                           I. A BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF THE MAJOR</h2></center><BR>

The radio and television course of study is designed primarily to prepare Christian students to serve the
Lord in Missionary broadcasting and in domestic Christian radio and television stations as technicians,
performers, producers, writers, and managers.  Special emphasis is also given to the business aspects of
broadcasting and to broadcast journalism skills because those whom the Lord allows to rise to prominence
in the broadcast media have exceptional opportunity for public testimony and to be a positive influence
for righteousness in their communities.



<hr><center><h2>                                  II. COURSE HIGHLIGHTS</h2></center><BR>

Here are some of the courses in the program you will especially enjoy--<br>
<P>
        Fundamentals of Broadcasting  This course will give you a picture of the industry--its
        History, organization, economics, and program structure.  You will receive practical
        experience in creating, directing, and performing radio and television programs.
<P>
        Audio and Video Equipment Operation  In these courses you will learn the operation of
        standard studio equipment, mixing, recording, tape-editing, and station procedures.
<P>
        Broadcast News  Here you will gain experience with the organization and operation of
        the News department, gathering and writing News, building various types of News
        programs, instruction and practice in announcing News, News services, and handling of
        wire copy.


<hr><center><h2>                          III. A TYPICAL YEARLY COURSE SEQUENCE</h2></center><BR>

This is a suggested program of study for you.  You understand that other refinements to your program
can be made when you consult your faculty advisor at the time of your enrollment.
<P>
You will notice that some courses are listed as electives.  These electives give you the opportunity to
tailor your program to (1) secure the equivalent of a double major by adding additional courses to your
selected minor field of study, (2) add a third field of interest to your program of study which is almost
the same as having two minors, or (3) broaden your program by selecting individual courses you would
like to take to help you in your future ministry or for your own personal enjoyment.
<PRE>
