<hr><center><h2>                 IV. FACILITIES, EQUIPMENT, AND OPPORTUNITIES </h2></center><BR>

Performance Hall productions use the 140-seat thrust theatre in the Speech Building that provides for
four or five Student-directed performances each semester.  The repertoire includes sacred drama as well
as secular drama from the classics.  Through periodic auditions, many Students (including underclassmen)
are chosen for major and minor roles in these highly regarded, often sold-out productions.
<P>
Several major University productions are presented in the 2,600-seat Rodeheaver Auditorium, which
is one of the best equipped in the Southeast.  The mechanical equipment includes two electrically
controlled contour curtains, a revolving stage, and orchestra and stage lifts.  The building also contains
the scene shop, storage docks, the extensive wardrobe for all productions, and dressing rooms and
property rooms.
<P>
The twice-monthly Sunday Vesper programs, sacred programs of music, speech, and drama, will
provide you opportunities for valuable performance experience.
<P>
Fine Arts Contests in music, speech, art, and literature are held annually, and all Students have an
opportunity to compete in them.  Awards are given to winners in the field of piano, men's voice,
women's voice, organ, string, woodwind, brass, original oratory, dramatic reading, poetry, art,
photography, extemporaneous essay, and original hymn text writing.
<P>
The Classic Players is one of the outstanding college Shakespearean repertoire groups in the world.  If
you are interested, you should try out for this group when tryouts are held in the fall.  Two major
productions are presented each year, including such great plays as HAMLET, JULIUS CAESAR,
MACBETH, THE TAMING OF THE SHREW, and THE MERCHANT OF VENICE.
<P>
The University Debate Association provides opportunity for you to compete in debate as a member of
your society.  Each society participates in several elimination contests throughout the school year to
determine the winner of the University cup which is awarded during Commencement week.  The
University also sponsors debate teams which compete in tournaments several times throughout the year.
Over the years our teams have established an outstanding record and an excellent reputation in
competition at the national and regional levels.
<P>
The University's drama ensemble, Truth in Action, travels for a semester or a summer, presenting the
Gospel in churches and schools across America.
<P>
The University's film production unit, Unusual Films, often calls on the University student body to
participate in the many aspects of motion picture production.
<P>
Through the daily Chapel program and special public affairs meetings, you will have the privilege
of observing and learning from some of the finest speakers and preachers in the nation as they address
the Student body.
<P>
<a href="/aboutbju/places/library/">The modern Mack Library</A>, with 90,000 square feet of floor space and seating for over 1400 Students,
will give you access to 231,000 volumes, 1100 current periodical subscriptions, and more than 10,500
recordings.  An interlibrary loan program is available through OCLC, a national database, for books not
held in our library.
<P>
<a href="/aboutbju/places/fitness/">The Fremont Fitness Center gives you</A> the opportunity to enjoy the benefits of a health club right on
Campus at no additional cost to you.  You can keep yourself in top-notch physical condition through the
use of its state-of-the-art exercise equipment, racquetball courts, spa, and sauna.
<P>
If you are planning to live on Campus, you will be glad to know that <a href="/studentlife/dorm/">all of our Dormitories are</A>air-
conditioned, have wall-to-wall carpeting, and have a phone in each room.  You will be able to make long-
distance calls home directly from your room and have them automatically placed on your school bill.
<P>
All of our classrooms are air-conditioned, and there are awnings over the sidewalks to keep you dry when
it is raining.  <a href="/whatsnew/menu/">The Dining Common serves 8,500 delicious meals</A> a day, and the Snack Shop and
Bookstore <a href="/aboutbju/places/stucenter/">in the Student Center</a> carry just about anything you'll need.
<P>
You will find the finest Christian young people in the country are your fellow Students, and without
trying too hard, you may end up marrying one of them!


<hr><center><h2>                             V. ABOUT THE FACULTY</h2></center><BR>

Under an expert faculty who have many years of experience, you will receive a strong combination of
thorough classroom training and intensive "hands on" training in the University's cocurricular program.
Our speech faculty have done postgraduate work at such schools as the University of Michigan, Purdue
University, Louisiana State University, the University of Alabama, and Southern Illinois University.
<P>
The University maintains a speech clinic with a qualified speech therapist.  In addition, our speech faculty
have participated with professional and regional speech programs, and one of our public speaking faculty
members is a nationally recognized parliamentarian and has held office with the American Association
of Parliamentarians.


<hr><center><h2>                    VI. CAREER OPPORTUNITIES AND PLACEMENT</h2></center><BR>

Many of our graduates have used the rhetoric and public address major in preparation for law school,
in combination as a double major with Bible for a dynamic preaching ministry, or for a career in sales,
public relations, communications consulting, radio, or writing.  Of course, this major can also be used
to prepare you for a teaching ministry in either the public or private field at either the high school or
college level.  Graduates from our speech programs are on the faculties of most of the major Fundamental
Christian Colleges and universities.


<hr><center><h2>                      VII. BJU:  AN AFFORDABLE EDUCATION</h2></center><BR>

Enclosed is an expense sheet detailing the cost of attending Bob Jones University.  When you compare
our charges to those of other private Colleges, we think you will be pleasantly surprised.  We believe we
offer a Student more value for his dollar than anyone else in America.  And to help you see how
affordable "the Opportunity Place" can be for you, we have enclosed a financial analysis form that you
can use to evaluate your own situation.  Your Admissions Counselor or the Director of Student Financial
Aid would be happy to discuss this with you if you have any questions.
<hr><h2><center> HOW TO TAKE THE NEXT STEP. . . </h2></center>
<P>
If you can see yourself in the career described in the profile, then a great opportunity awaits you at
Bob Jones University.  It is the opportunity for the premier Christian college experience in all the world.
It is the opportunity for learning, for fun, and for developing New Friendships.  It is the opportunity to
prepare for a lifetime of service for the Lord . . .
<P>
Simply fill out the <a href="/admissions/information/application.html">enclosed application form</a> and return it in the envelope provided.  Be sure to enclose
the small application fee.  Then get ready for a life-changing experience which more than 60,000 young
people already know about. . .
<p>
The Opportunity Place...God's Special Place for You.<BR>
