<hr><center><h2>             IV. FACILITIES, EQUIPMENT, AND OPPORTUNITIES</h2></center><BR>

Our Modern Language Laboratory, open six days a week from morning till night, contains the latest
state-of-the-art recording and listening equipment, providing you with a unique opportunity to perfect
your language skills.  We have 28 individual tape player/recorder stations plus another 7 stations which
are serviced by a control console.  Thus, we have the capaCity to play 30 different programs at any given
time.  The laboratory also features an Apple IIe computer.  You may use these facilities without paying
a lab fee.The materials in the language lab include a large repertory of assigned practice tapes and computer discs.
There are also numerous tapes available for Student study and enjoyment containing foreign literature,
poetry, cultural News, dialects, and music.  We hold subscriptions to a number of foreign newspapers and
periodicals and maintain a sizeable collection of foreign filmstrips with accompanying sound tapes.
Books, brochures, and posters round out the available materials, together with portable tape players and
film/slide projectors.
<P>
Through the means of placement test, students with prior exposure to Spanish will be placed at their
level of study.  Very often we have in our classes some foreign nationals from Spanish-speaking
countries.  They are challenged by our upper-level instruction, and at the same time other Students profit
from their presence in the classrooms.
<P>
The Spanish Club meets biweekly.  Here you will practice your language skills in an informal
atmosphere of songs, skits, travelogues, films, and other presentations.
<P>
A special event is held in February of each year when the modern language department presents an
evening of entertainment and instruction (sometimes plays) in French, German, and Spanish.
<P>
Missionary teams going to Spanish-speaking countries are sponsored by the University every year.  You
may have opportunity to participate in this outreach.
<P>
In child evangelism classes, our Students teach children songs and Bible verses in foreign languages or
minister to foreign-speaking children in their native tongue.
<P>
Since Greenville has a sizeable international community, our Students have ample opportunity to use
their language skills in interaction with native speakers.
<P>
<a href="/whatsnew/chapel/">Chapel services are held every morning</A>, Monday through Friday.  These services are a source of great
inspiration to Students.  Four days a week the Chapel message is brought by the Chancellor or <a href="/aboutbju/president/">President</a>
when on the Campus, and in their absence by selected speakers.  One day each week the Chapel period
is devoted to the meetings of various literary societies.  Two meetings each month are devoted to
Missionary programs and speakers.
<P>
<a href="/aboutbju/places/fitness/">The Fremont Fitness Center gives you</A> the opportunity to enjoy the benefits of a health club right on
Campus at no additional cost to you.  You can keep yourself in top-notch physical condition through the
use of its state-of-the-art exercise equipment, racquetball courts, spa, and sauna.
<P>
<a href="/aboutbju/places/library/">The modern Mack Library</A>, with 90,000 square feet of floor space and seating for over 1400 Students,
will give you access to 231,000 volumes, 1100 current periodical subscriptions, and more than 10,500
recordings.  An interlibrary loan program is available through OCLC, a national database, for books not
held in our library.
<P>
If you are planning to live on Campus, you will be glad to know that <a href="/studentlife/dorm/">all of our Dormitories are</A>air-
conditioned, have wall-to-wall carpeting, and have a phone in each room.  You will be able to make long-
distance calls home directly from your room and have them automatically placed on your school bill.
<P>
All of our classrooms are air-conditioned, and there are awnings over the sidewalks to keep you dry when
it is raining.  <a href="/whatsnew/menu/">The Dining Common serves 8,500 delicious meals</A> a day, and the Snack Shop and
Bookstore <a href="/aboutbju/places/stucenter/">in the Student Center</a> carry just about anything you'll need.You will find the finest Christian young people in the country are your fellow Students, and without
trying too hard, you may end up marrying one of them!


<hr><center><h2>                         V. ABOUT THE FACULTY</h2></center><BR>

Our foreign language faculty is well qualified to teach you.  All of our Spanish teachers hold either a
PH.D or master's degree from leading graduate schools throughout the country.  They have a combined
total of more than 60 years of teaching experience.  All of the teachers have native or near-native fluency
in Spanish, and all of them have traveled in Spanish-speaking countries and have developed an
understanding of the culture.


<hr><center><h2>                VI. CAREER OPPORTUNITIES AND PLACEMENT</h2></center><BR>

Some of the career opportunities available to you as a Spanish major include:<BR>
<LI> Teaching
<LI> Missions
<LI> Interpretation (oral) and Translation (written)
<LI> Manufacturer's representative at home or abroad
<LI> International - airlines, banking, industry, business, journalism
<LI> Government service - State Department, Foreign Service, Department of Defense, Department
   of Agriculture
<LI> Military
<LI> Social services among foreign minority in the United States - Florida, New York, and the
Southwestern states have large Spanish-speaking populations
<P>
In the Greenville/Spartanburg metropolitan area there are several Spanish international companies with
need for bilingual and trilingual personnel.  Most metropolitan areas have similar situations.  Some of
our graduates pursue advanced degrees before entering the job market.


<hr><center><h2>                  VII. BJU:  AN AFFORDABLE EDUCATION</h2></center><BR>

Enclosed is an expense sheet detailing the cost of attending Bob Jones University.  When you compare
our charges to those of other private Colleges, we think you will be pleasantly surprised.  We believe we
offer a Student more value for his dollar than anyone else in America.  And to help you see how
affordable "the Opportunity Place" can be for you, we have enclosed a financial analysis form that you
can use to evaluate your own situation.  Your Admissions Counselor or the Director of Student Financial
Aid would be happy to discuss this with you if you have any questions.

<hr><center><h2>                        HOW TO TAKE THE NEXT STEP. . . </h2></center>

If you can see yourself in the career described in the profile, then a great opportunity awaits you at
Bob Jones University.  It is the opportunity for the premier Christian college experience in all the world.
It is the opportunity for learning, for fun, and for developing New Friendships.  It is the opportunity to
prepare for a lifetime of service for the Lord . . .
<P>
Simply fill out the <a href="/admissions/information/application.html">enclosed application form</a> and return it in the envelope provided.  Be sure to enclose
the small application fee.  Then get ready for a life-changing experience which more than 60,000 young
people already know about. . .
<p>
The Opportunity Place...God's Special Place for You.<BR>
