<HEAD>
<TITLE> Technical Writing major </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body><br><br><center><img src="/graphics/bjcrest.gif"></center><br>

<hr><center><h2>                  I. A BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF THE MAJOR</h2></center><BR>

The technical writing major exists to meet the need for skilled writers of expository prose in business and
the professions.


<hr><center><h2>                         II. COURSE HIGHLIGHTS</h2></center><BR>

Here are some of the courses in the program you will especially enjoy--<br>
<P>
     Principles of Communication  This course surveys the process, theory, and philosophy
     of contemporary verbal and non-verbal communication.
<P>
     Expository Writing  Here you will learn the principles and techniques of writing that
     informs or explains.
<P>

     Book Editing  In this class you will learn the policies and practices of the editor,
     including the processing of copy and page makeup with special emphasis on audience
     analysis, author/editor relations, advance planning, circulation, and promotion.
<P>

     Fundamentals of Technical Writing  This course introduces you to basic principles and
     techniques of writing for science, industry, and the professions.



<hr><center><h2>                 III. A TYPICAL YEARLY COURSE SEQUENCE</h2></center><BR>

This is a suggested program of study for you.  You understand that other refinements to your program
can be made when you consult your faculty advisor at the time of your enrollment.
<P>
You will notice that some courses are listed as electives.  These electives give you the opportunity to
tailor your program to (1) secure the equivalent of a double major by adding additional courses to your
selected minor field of study, (2) add a third field of interest to your program of study which is almost
the same as having two minors, or (3) broaden your program by selecting individual courses you would
like to take to help you in your future ministry or for your own personal enjoyment.<BR>
<pre>
Freshman
 Orientation                    1   Orientation                       1
 Composition and Rhetoric*      3   Composition and Literature*       3
 Foreign Language               3   Foreign Language                  3
 Computer Applications I        3   Computer Applications II          3
 History of Civilization        3   History of Civilization           3
 Principles of Christian Growth 1   Principles of Bible Study         1
 Minor or Electives             3   Fundamentals of Speech            3
 Total                         17   Total                            17

Sophomore
 American or British Literature 3   Fundamentals of Technical Writing 3
 Principles of Communication    3   Graphics                          3
 Expository Writing             3   Foreign Language                  3
 Foreign Language               3   New Testament Messages            1
 Old Testament Messages         1   Minor or Electives                6
 Minor or Electives             3   Total                            16
 Total                         16

Junior
 Book Editing                   3   Business Writing                  3
 Philosophy or Psychology**     3   Philosophy or Psychology**        3
 Bible Doctrines                3   Christian Living Forum            1
 Minor or Electives             6   Bible Doctrines                   3
 Total                         15   Minor or Electives                5
                                    Total                            15

Senior
 Advanced Technical Writing     3   Writing Internship or Professional
 Writing Seminar                1    Writing and Publication Elective*3
 Bible Elective                 2   Bible Elective                    2
 Oral Communication             2   Minor or Electives               11
 Minor or Electives             8   Total                            16
 Total                         16
____________
</pre>

* If you do not place out of En 100, you will begin your English sequence with the Composition and Grammar course.<BR>

** You will take six hours in one of these subjects.<BR>

*** Specific assignments are made at department chairman's discretion.<BR>


<hr><center><h2>             IV. FACILITIES, EQUIPMENT, AND OPPORTUNITIES</h2></center><BR>

The Writing Seminar is a discussion course you will take during your senior year.  It is designed to
round out and firm up your Christian view of writing methods and goals.


Through the various Campus media, you will have the advantage of receiving experience and using the
facilities in such highly developed Ministries as Unusual Films, radio station WMUU, and the University
BJU Press.  You will have the opportunity to work closely with technically trained personnel in their
vocational fields and to see their best work in print or performed on stage, radio, or film.A modern computer lab enables you to learn up-to-date electronic procedures for generating and
processing written text.
<P>
The Fundamentalism File in the Mack Library will provide a wealth of background materials for you
to acquaint yourself with the history of the movement.
<P>
The Professional Internship places you with an organization that will give you on-the-job experience
in the areas of your specialization.
<P>
Our Modern Language Laboratory, open six days a week, contains the latest state-of-the-art recording
and listening equipment, providing you with a unique opportunity to perfect your language skills.  We
have 28 individual tape player/recorder stations plus another 7 stations which are serviced by a control
console.  Thus, we have the capaCity to play 30 different programs at any given time.  The laboratory
also features an Apple IIe computer.  You may use these facilities without paying a lab fee.
<P>
<a href="/whatsnew/chapel/">Chapel services are held every morning</A>, Monday through Friday.  These services are a source of great
inspiration to Students.  Four days a week the Chapel message is brought by the Chancellor or <a href="/aboutbju/president/">President</a>
when on the Campus, and in their absence by selected speakers.  One day each week the Chapel period
is devoted to the meetings of various literary societies.  Two meetings each month are devoted to
Missionary programs and speakers.
<P>
The annual spring <a href="/special/bibleconf/">Bible Conference</a> is one of the outstanding features of the University and Academy
year.  Your regular academic work will be suspended for the Conference, during which you will hear
messages from outstanding Bible teachers, pastors, and evangelists.
<P>
<a href="/aboutbju/places/fitness/">The Fremont Fitness Center gives you</A> the opportunity to enjoy the benefits of a health club right on
Campus at no additional cost to you.  You can keep yourself in top-notch physical condition through the
use of its state-of-the-art exercise equipment, racquetball courts, spa, and sauna.
<P>
<a href="/aboutbju/places/library/">The modern Mack Library</A>, with 90,000 square feet of floor space and seating for over 1400 Students,
will give you access to 231,000 volumes, 1100 current periodical subscriptions, and more than 10,500
recordings.  An interlibrary loan program is available through OCLC, a national database, for books not
held in our library.
<P>
If you are planning to live on Campus, you will be glad to know that <a href="/studentlife/dorm/">all of our Dormitories are</A>air-
conditioned, have wall-to-wall carpeting, and have a phone in each room.  You will be able to make long-
distance calls home directly from your room and have them automatically placed on your school bill.
<P>
All of our classrooms are air-conditioned, and there are awnings over the sidewalks to keep you dry when
it is raining.  <a href="/whatsnew/menu/">The Dining Common serves 8,500 delicious meals</A> a day, and the Snack Shop and
Bookstore <a href="/aboutbju/places/stucenter/">in the Student Center</a> carry just about anything you'll need.
<P>
You will find the finest Christian young people in the country are your fellow Students, and without
trying too hard, you may end up marrying one of them!
<hr><h2><center> V. ABOUT THE FACULTY </h2></center>
<P>
The courses of the Department of Professional Writing and Publication are taught by experts in the theory
and skills they teach.  All of these professors have graduate degrees and years of experience in teaching
the elements of writing and writing production.  They are all authors, and together they have written
many books and articles.  They have been advisors to publications, and all have had experience in
editorial consulting.
<P>

<hr><center><h2>                VI. CAREER OPPORTUNITIES AND PLACEMENT</h2></center><BR>

As a major in technical writing, you will be prepared to enter a number of fields in mass communication
and, as a Christian, make your impact felt.  Among these fields are the following:
<P>
Newspapers
Magazines
Textbooks
Films
Radio programs
Audiovisual
Advertising
Public relations
Mass media
Television
<hr><center><h2>                  VII. BJU:  AN AFFORDABLE EDUCATION </h2></center><BR>

Enclosed is an expense sheet detailing the cost of attending Bob Jones University.  When you compare
our charges to those of other private Colleges, we think you will be pleasantly surprised.  We believe we
offer a Student more value for his dollar than anyone else in America.  And to help you see how
affordable "the Opportunity Place" can be for you, we have enclosed a financial analysis form that you
can use to evaluate your own situation.  Your Admissions Counselor or the Director of Student Financial
Aid would be happy to discuss this with you if you have any questions.


<hr><center><h2>                    HOW TO TAKE THE NEXT STEP. . .</h2></center><BR>

If you can see yourself in the career described in the profile, then a great opportunity awaits you at
Bob Jones University.  It is the opportunity for the premier Christian college experience in all the world.
It is the opportunity for learning, for fun, and for developing New Friendships.  It is the opportunity to
prepare for a lifetime of service for the Lord . . .
<P>
Simply fill out the <a href="/admissions/information/application.html">enclosed application form</a> and return it in the envelope provided.  Be sure to enclose
the small application fee.  Then get ready for a life-changing experience which more than 60,000 young
people already know about. . .
<p>
The Opportunity Place...God's Special Place for You.<BR>
