<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Rodeheaver Auditorium</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><H1>Rodeheaver Auditorium</H1></CENTER>
<BR><CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/horiz.gif"></CENTER><BR>
The Rodeheaver Auditorium is one of the
best equipped and most modem in the Southeast.
The mechanical equipment of the building is the
finest in the entire South and includes two electrically controlled contour curtains, a revolving
stage, and orchestra and stage lifts, which are the
largest of their types ever designed. Seating almost 3,000 people, this building also contains
the scene shop, storage docks, the extensive
wardrobe for all productions, as well as dressing
rooms and property rooms. A 57-rank Zimmer
pipe organ is also located in this hall. Rodeheaver Auditorium also houses Unusual Films.
<BR><BR>
<CENTER>
