<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Fine Arts Building</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><H1>Fine Arts Building</H1></CENTER>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/horiz.gif"></CENTER><BR>
The Fine Arts Building contains specially designed studios for voice, piano, instruments,
and pipe organ, as well as practice halls for orchestra, band, chorus, and ensembles. The Music
Library, with its large record, compact disc, videocassette, and score collection, is also located
here. Art facilities include offices, classrooms, and studios for painting and drawing, sculpture,
ceramics, and graphic arts. Radio and Television
Broadcasting Department facilities include classrooms, control rooms, radio studios, broadcast
engineering laboratory classrooms, and a well equipped laboratory television studio. The
studios of student operated WBJU, the campus FM radio station, are also located in the Fine
Arts Building.

