<html>
 <head>
   <title>How do I?</title>
   <meta name="Author" content="Jonathan Pait">
   <meta name="GENERATOR" content="Mozilla/2.0GoldB1 (Win32)"> </head>
 <body text="#000000" link="#0000FF" vlink="#551A8B" alink="#FF0000" background="pic/gray.jpg">


<hr         width="100%"><font SIZE=+3>How does this work?</font>&nbsp;

<hr         width="100%">
 To view graphical illustrations of the below instructions, <a href="how_grph.html">click
here</a> (low speed connections beware!) <br> <br>
 1. At the home page of the Linked Word Project
 choose the book you wish to view. &nbsp;You may choose the book from the table by placing
your cursor over the book you wish to read and clicking. <br> <br>
 2. That will take you to the chapter index for the book you choose.
 Once there you click on the chapter you wish to read. <br> <br>
 3. Your hypertext options continue once you are viewing the text of
 the chapter you chose. &nbsp;Notice the <a HREF="what.html">asterisks</a>: they will take
you to a page listing the greek parsing for the verb preceding it. <br> <br>
 4. The options continue! You will notice that every word of the text
 has a link. &nbsp;By clicking on any word in the text you can learn its lexicon meaning. 
<br> <br>
 5. Once you have viewed the information you wish to see, the fastest
 way to get back to the chapter you were reading is to press the BACK button of your browser.
&nbsp;However, the <img src="pic/hom.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0  height=24 width =25

align=center >&nbsp;button
 will take you to the original index. <br>
 <br>6. When you reach the end of a chapter and wish to continue reading
 in the next chapter, press the <img src="pic/nxt.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0  height=24

width =25 align=center >&nbsp;button.

<br>
 <br>7. You may also return to the chapter preceding the chapter you are reading by pressing
the <img src="pic/pre.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0 height=24 width =25 align=center>&nbsp;button. <br>
 <hr width="100%"> <center>
 <br><a href="index.html"><img src="pic/hom.jpg" alt="Home" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0 
height=24 width=25 ></a>&nbsp;<a href="in.html"><img src="pic/hlp.jpg" alt="Help" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0 height=24 width=25></a></center>

</body>
</html>

