<html>
<head>
   <title>How do I? (Graphical)</title>
   <meta name="Author" content="Jonathan Pait">
   <meta name="GENERATOR" content="Mozilla/2.0GoldB1 (Win32)">
</head>
<body text="#000000" bgcolor="#C0C0C0" link="#0000FF" vlink="#551A8B" alink="#FF0000" background="pic/gray.jpg">

<p>
<hr         width="100%"><font SIZE=+3>How does this work?</font>&nbsp;

<hr         width="100%">1. At the home page of the Linked Word Project
choose the book you wish to view. 
<br>
<br><img src="pic/str.jpg" alt="To start:  Simply click on the chapter you wish to view." hspace=5 vspace=5 border=2  height=312 width =414 align=bottom >
<br></p>

<p>2. That will take you to the chapter index for the book you choose.
Once there you click on the chapter you wish to read.</p>

<p><img src="pic/str2.jpg" alt="Then you choose the chapter you wish to view." hspace=5 vspace=5 border=2  height=283 width =489 >
<br>
<br>3. Your hypertext options continue once you are viewing the text of
the chapter you chose. &nbsp;Notice the <a HREF="what.html">astericks</a>:
they will take you to a page listing the greek parsing for the verb preceding
it. 
<br>
<br><img src="pic/str3.jpg" alt="Clicking on the asterick takes you to the greek parsing." hspace=5 vspace=5 border=2  height=312 width =492 >
<br>
<br>4. The options continue! You will notice that every word of the text
has a link. &nbsp;By clicking on any word in the text you can learn its
lexicon meaning. 
<br>
<br><img src="pic/str4.jpg" alt="Every word has a link to a lexicon entry!" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=2  height=270 width =494 >
<br>
<br>5. Once you have viewed the information you wish to see, the fastest
way to get back to the chapter you were reading is to press the <img src="pic/back.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0  height=20 width =50 align=center >button
of your browser. &nbsp;However, the <img src="pic/hom.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0  height=24 width =25 align=center >&nbsp;button
will take you to the original index. 
<br>
<br>6. When you reach the end of a chapter and wish to continue reading
in the next chapter, press the <img src="pic/nxt.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0  height=24 width =25 align=center >&nbsp;button.

<br>
<br>7. You may also return to the chapter preceding the chapter you are
reading by pressing the <img src="pic/pre.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0  height=24 width =25 align=center >&nbsp;button.
<br>
