<pre>

<br><br><hr><a name=3200><br>3200</a><p> membrana {mem-bran'-ah}
of Latin origin ("membrane") ; n f

 AV - parchment 1; 1

 1) parchment, made first of dressed skins at Pergamos, hence its name


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=3201><br>3201</a><p> memphomai {mem'-fom-ahee}
middle voice of an apparently root word ; TDNT - 4:571,580; v

 AV - find fault 3; 3

 1) to blame, find fault


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=3202><br>3202</a><p> mempsimoiros {mem-psim'-oy-ros}
from a presumed derivative of <a href="3200.html#3201"<br>3201</a> and moira (fate, akin to the base of 3313) ; TDNT - 4:571,580; adj

 AV - complainer 1; 1

 1) complaining of one's lot, querulous, discontented


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
